column1:
Select drinker
From frequents
Where drinker
NOT IN (
  Select drinker
  From ((
    Select frequents.drinker, frequents.bar, serves.beer
    From serves
    JOIN frequents
    ON serves.bar = frequents.bar)
    EXCEPT (
      Select likes.drinker, frequents.bar, likes.beer
      From likes
      JOIN frequents
      ON likes.drinker = frequents.drinker))AS V);
/*Every person goes to at least one bar that serves
more drinks than what they like so the query will
return 0*/

/*(i) Find names of all drinkers who frequent only those bars that serve only beers they like.

#all drinker EXCEPT
#drinkers who frequent bars that serve ANY beer they dislike
	#find beers that drinker dislikes
	#repeat h with that instead of likes

NEED ALL DRINKERS EXCEPT (WORKS)

#WORKS:
#dislikes.name = beer
#SELECT DISTINCT dislike_serve.beer, dislike_serve.drinker FROM

*/

/* (DRINKER, DISLIKES) */
SELECT drinker.name as drinker FROM drinker 
EXCEPT 
SELECT DISTINCT frequents.drinker /*, frequents.bar */FROM 
	frequents
	INNER JOIN
	/*bars frequented UNION dislike_bars gives us a list of drinkers who frequent bars that serve beers they dislike*/
	(SELECT dislike_bars.drinker as drinker,/* dislike_bars.beer as beer, */ dislike_bars.bar as bar FROM (
		SELECT * FROM (
			SELECT drinker.name as drinker, beer.name as beer1 FROM beer CROSS JOIN drinker
			EXCEPT 
			SELECT likes.drinker as drinker, likes.beer as beer1 FROM likes 
		) as dislikers
		/* must now be matched with bars that serve dislikes */
	INNER JOIN 
		serves
	ON serves.beer = dislikers.beer1
	) as dislike_bars)
	as badness
	ON frequents.drinker=badness.drinker AND frequents.bar=badness.bar

column1:
with A(drinker, bar, beer) as
(select drinker, bar, beer
from frequents natural join serves),

B(drinker, bar, beer) as
(select drinker, bar, beer
from serves natural join likes)

(select name
from drinker)
except
(select drinker
from A
where not exists (
select *
from B
where A.drinker=B.drinker
and A.bar=B.bar
and A.beer=B.beer));

column1:
SELECT name FROM Drinker
WHERE NOT EXISTS
	(SELECT bar FROM Frequents
	WHERE drinker = name AND EXISTS
		(SELECT beer FROM Serves
		WHERE Serves.bar = Frequents.bar
		AND beer NOT IN
			(SELECT beer FROM Likes
			WHERE drinker = name)));

column1:
(SELECT name FROM drinker)

EXCEPT

(SELECT drinker FROM ((SELECT drinker, bar FROM frequents) INTERSECT (SELECT drinker, bar FROM

  ((SELECT drinker, s1.beer, bar FROM serves AS s1, likes AS l1 WHERE s1.beer <> l1.beer)

  EXCEPT

  ((SELECT drinker, s1.beer, bar FROM serves AS s1, likes AS l1 WHERE s1.beer = l1.beer))) AS F

)) AS T);

-- (i) Find names of all drinkers who frequent only those bars that serve only beers they like.

--Find drinkers who frequent bars that serve some beers they don't like


--ALL drinkers - people who go to bars that serve some beer they don't like

SELECT DISTINCT name FROM drinker

EXCEPT

SELECT a.drinker FROM (
  (SELECT drinker, beer FROM
    frequents JOIN serves ON frequents.bar = serves.bar)
    EXCEPT
  (SELECT drinker, beer FROM likes)
) a;

--Find names of all drinkers who frequent only those bars that
--serve only beers they like

--Discussed RA translation with other students

SELECT DISTINCT name FROM Drinker
--diff
EXCEPT (
  SELECT h.drinker FROM
  --Select drinker, bar from Frequents
  (SELECT Frequents.drinker, Serves.beer FROM
    (Frequents NATURAL JOIN Serves)
  --diff
  EXCEPT (
    (SELECT * FROM Likes))) AS h
);

SELECT DISTINCT name FROM Drinker
EXCEPT (
  SELECT T.drinker FROM
  (SELECT Frequents.drinker, Serves.beer From
        (Frequents NATURAL JOIN Serves)
EXCEPT (
  SELECT * FROM Likes)) as T
);

column1:
select distinct name
from drinker
where drinker.name not in
(select drinker
  from frequents, serves
  where frequents.bar=serves.bar and not exists
  (
  select * from likes
  where frequents.bar=serves.bar and frequents.drinker=likes.drinker and likes.beer=serves.beer
));

select d.name as drinker from drinker d except
(select drinker from 
(
(select f.drinker, f.bar, s.beer from frequents f, serves s
where f.bar = s.bar) 
EXCEPT 
(select l.drinker,s.bar, l.beer from likes l, serves s
where l.beer = s.beer)
)
as d);

Select distinct name
from drinker
except
-- get the drinkers who frequent bars who offer 0 drinks they like
Select distinct tbl1.drinker
From
(
	Select a.drinker, b.beer
	from frequents a, serves b
	where a.bar = b.bar
	EXCEPT
	select drinker,beer
	from likes
) tbl1;

(
  SELECT
    name AS drinker
  FROM
    drinker
)
EXCEPT
(
  SELECT
    temp3.drinker
  FROM
  (
    (
      SELECT
        drinker, bar
      FROM
        frequents
    )
    EXCEPT
    (
      SELECT
        temp2.drinker, temp2.bar
      FROM
        (
          (
            SELECT
              DISTINCT s1.drinker, s2.bar
            FROM
              likes AS s1, serves AS s2
          )
          EXCEPT
          (
            SELECT
              temp.drinker, temp.bar
            FROM
              (
                (
                  SELECT
                    DISTINCT s1.drinker, s2.beer, s2.bar
                  FROM
                    likes AS s1, serves AS s2
                )
                EXCEPT
                (
                  SELECT
                    drinker, beer, bar
                  FROM
                  (
                    likes NATURAL JOIN serves
                  )
                )
              ) AS temp
          )
        ) AS temp2
    )
  ) AS temp3
);

(SELECT name
FROM drinker)
EXCEPT
SELECT DISTINCT d.name
FROM drinker AS d, frequents AS f, serves AS s
WHERE f.drinker = d.name
AND s.bar = f.bar
AND s.beer NOT IN (
  SELECT beer
  FROM likes as l
  WHERE l.drinker = d.name
);

column1:
SELECT name as drinker 
FROM drinker 
EXCEPT 
SELECT t.drinker 
FROM (
    (SELECT frequents.drinker, frequents.bar, serves.beer 
    FROM frequents 
    JOIN serves 
    ON frequents.bar=serves.bar)
    EXCEPT
    (SELECT frequents.drinker,frequents.bar,serves.beer 
    FROM frequents 
    JOIN serves on frequents.bar=serves.bar 
    JOIN likes 
    ON frequents.drinker=likes.drinker AND serves.beer=likes.beer)
) AS t 
GROUP BY drinker;

(SELECT drinker
FROM frequents))

FROM frequents)

FROM frequents, (SELECT serves.bar AS b, d 
		FROM serves, ((SELECT drinker.name AS d, beer.name

		WHERE serves.beer=dislike.name) AS dislikedBars
WHERE frequents.bar=b AND frequents.drinker=d));

/*Find names of all drinkers who frequent only those bars that serve only beers they like*/

(SELECT name FROM drinker)
EXCEPT
(SELECT DISTINCT sub2.drinker 
FROM (frequents
       NATURAL JOIN 
       (SELECT DISTINCT sub1.drinker, sub1.bar
        FROM ((SELECT drinker, serves.beer, bar FROM likes, serves WHERE likes.beer <> serves.beer)
            EXCEPT
            (SELECT drinker, likes.beer, bar FROM likes, serves WHERE likes.beer = serves.beer))
            AS sub1)
       AS sub)
       AS sub2);

column1:
SELECT name
FROM drinker    --why not acceptable to do SELECT drinker FROM frequents?
WHERE NOT EXISTS   
	(SELECT frequents.bar
		FROM frequents, serves
		WHERE frequents.drinker = drinker.name and frequents.bar = serves.bar
		AND serves.beer NOT IN (SELECT beer from likes WHERE drinker = drinker.name)); -- beer is NOT liked by drinker, 
																					--so NOT IN implies ALL beers are LIKED by the drinker

column1:
--Take all drinkers
(SELECT name
FROM Drinker)
--Remove drinkers who frequent bars serving drinks they don't like
EXCEPT
(SELECT drinker AS name
FROM ((SELECT Frequents.drinker, Serves.beer --All drinker, beer pairs where the drinker goes to a bar that serves the beer
		FROM Frequents, Likes, Serves
		WHERE Frequents.drinker=Likes.drinker AND Frequents.bar=Serves.bar)
		--Remove all drinker, beer pairs where drinker likes the beer
		--Leaves us with all drinker, beer pairs where drinker doesn't like the beer but it is served in a bar they go to
		EXCEPT
		(SELECT Frequents.drinker, Likes.beer
		FROM Frequents, Likes
		WHERE Frequents.drinker=Likes.drinker)) AS M);

SELECT DISTINCT name FROM Drinker EXCEPT
SELECT DISTINCT drinker FROM
(SELECT DISTINCT f.drinker, r.bar, r.beer
FROM Frequents f, Serves r
WHERE f.bar = r.bar
EXCEPT
SELECT DISTINCT l.drinker, s.bar, s.beer
FROM Likes l, Serves s
WHERE l.beer = s.beer) as foo;

SELECT DISTINCT name
  FROM drinker
  WHERE NOT EXISTS
  (SELECT serves.bar FROM serves, frequents WHERE frequents.bar=serves.bar AND drinker.name=frequents.drinker AND
    serves.beer NOT IN(SELECT likes.beer FROM likes WHERE drinker.name=likes.drinker));

column1:
SELECT name FROM drinker 
	EXCEPT (SELECT DISTINCT drinker FROM 
		(SELECT drinker, bar FROM frequents EXCEPT
		       	(SELECT drinker, bar FROM frequents except (
				SELECT DISTINCT name, bar FROM
			       	(SELECT name, bar, beer FROM drinker,serves except
				       	(SELECT likes.drinker, bar, serves.beer FROM serves,likes WHERE(likes.beer = serves.beer))) AS antilike))) AS badbar);

column1:
SELECT DISTINCT name
FROM drinker as f
WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT f2.bar
	FROM frequents as f2, serves
	WHERE f2.drinker=f.name
	AND f2.bar=serves.bar
	AND serves.beer NOT IN (SELECT beer FROM likes
			WHERE likes.drinker=f.name));

WITH notLoyalDrinkerBeerBar AS
((SELECT drinker, s1.beer, bar FROM serves AS s1, likes AS l1 WHERE s1.beer <> l1.beer)
EXCEPT
((SELECT drinker, s1.beer, bar FROM serves AS s1, likes AS l1 WHERE s1.beer = l1.beer))),

notLoyalDrinkerBar AS
((SELECT drinker, bar FROM frequents) INTERSECT (SELECT drinker, bar FROM notLoyalDrinkerBeerBar))

(SELECT name FROM drinker) EXCEPT (SELECT drinker FROM notLoyalDrinkerBar);

WITH LAMEDRINKERS(drinker, bar, beer) AS
(
  SELECT TOP.drinker, TOP.bar, TOP.beer
  FROM
  (
    SELECT frequents.drinker, frequents.bar, serves.beer
    FROM frequents, serves
    WHERE frequents.bar = serves.bar
  ) TOP
  EXCEPT
  SELECT BOTTOM.drinker, BOTTOM.bar, BOTTOM.beer
  FROM
  (
    SELECT frequents.drinker, frequents.bar, likes.beer
    FROM frequents, likes
    WHERE frequents.drinker = likes.drinker
  ) BOTTOM
)
SELECT drinker.name
FROM drinker
EXCEPT
SELECT LAMEDRINKERS.drinker
FROM LAMEDRINKERS;

/* Find names of all drinkers who frequent only those bars that serve only beers they like.
Bars which don't serve anything should not disqualify someone.
If a drinker doesn't frequent any bar, he or she should still be in the list vacuously. */

SELECT name
FROM drinker
WHERE name NOT IN (
    SELECT drinker
    FROM frequents AS f
    WHERE f.bar IN (
        SELECT bar
        FROM serves
        WHERE serves.beer NOT IN (
            SELECT beer
            FROM likes
            WHERE likes.drinker = f.drinker
        )
    )
);

with drink(drinker, bar, times_a_week, bar, beer, price) as (select * from frequents f, serves s where f.bar=s.bar except (select f.drinker, f.bar, f.times_a_week, s.bar, s.beer, s.price from frequents f, likes l, serves s where f.drinker=l.drinker and f.bar=s.bar and s.beer=l.beer)) 
select d.name from drinker d group by d.name except (select drinker from drink group by drinker);

column1:
(SELECT name FROM drinker)

EXCEPT

(SELECT DISTINCT drinker
FROM ((SELECT drinker, beer, frequents.bar
	 FROM frequents, serves
	 WHERE frequents.bar = serves.bar)

	 EXCEPT

	 (SELECT drinker, likes.beer, bar
	 FROM likes, serves
	 WHERE likes.beer = serves.beer)) AS T);

column1:
with pnlb(people,beer) as 
(select d.name, b.name from drinker d, beer b
where (d.name, b.name) not in 
(select drinker, beer from likes))

select name from drinker 
where name not in 
(select f.drinker from frequents f, serves s, pnlb p
where f.bar = s.bar and p.beer = s.beer and f.drinker = p.people);

column1:
SELECT name 
FROM drinker
EXCEPT (
SELECT drinker FROM((
SELECT drinker, beer
FROM frequents 
JOIN serves
ON frequents.bar = serves.bar) 
EXCEPT (SELECT * FROM likes)
) AS temp);

SELECT DISTINCT name AS drinker FROM Drinker
WHERE Drinker.name NOT IN 
(SELECT DISTINCT drinker FROM 
(SELECT Frequents.drinker AS drinker, Serves.bar AS bar, Serves.beer AS beer
FROM Serves
INNER JOIN Frequents ON Serves.bar = Frequents.bar
EXCEPT
SELECT Likes.drinker AS drinker, Frequents.bar AS bar, Likes.beer AS beer
FROM Likes 
INNER JOIN Frequents ON Likes.drinker = Frequents.drinker) AS derivedTable);

With BeersNotLiked(drinker, beer)as (select Drinker.name,Beer.name
from Drinker , Beer 
where (Drinker.name,Beer.name) not in (
select drinker,beer
from Likes)
)

select name
from Drinker
where name not in (
select Frequents.drinker
from Frequents, Serves,  BeersNotLiked as dis 
where  dis.beer = Serves.beer and Frequents.bar = Serves.bar and Frequents.drinker = dis.drinker );

FROM Drinker 
WHERE name NOT IN
(SELECT f1.drinker 
FROM SERVES s1, FREQUENTS f1 
WHERE s1.bar = f1.bar 
AND NOT EXISTS 
(SELECT * 
	FROM Likes l1 
	WHERE l1.drinker = f1.drinker 
	AND s1.beer = l1.beer));

column1:
SELECT DISTINCT name FROM drinker
EXCEPT
SELECT DISTINCT drinker
	FROM ((SELECT f.drinker, bar as fBar, beer as unlBeer
				FROM frequents as f 
					FULL OUTER JOIN 
					(SELECT drinker.name as drinker, beer.name as beer
						FROM drinker cross join beer
					EXCEPT
					SELECT * from likes) 
					as l
					ON f.drinker = l.drinker) as fAndL
					FULL OUTER JOIN serves as s
					ON fAndL.fbar = s.bar)
	WHERE unlbeer = beer

SELECT DISTINCT name
FROM drinker
WHERE name NOT IN (

SELECT DISTINCT drinker FROM
(
	((SELECT DISTINCT serves.bar, beer, drinker
	FROM frequents INNER JOIN serves
	ON frequents.bar = serves.bar ORDER BY drinker)
	EXCEPT
	(SELECT DISTINCT bar, likes.beer, drinker
	FROM serves INNER JOIN likes 
	ON serves.beer=likes.beer ORDER BY drinker))
) AS f1

);

column1:
WITH Dont_like AS
(SELECT DISTINCT Drinker.name AS drinker, Beer.name AS beer
FROM Beer, Drinker
EXCEPT
SELECT *
FROM Likes)
SELECT name AS drinker
FROM Drinker
EXCEPT
SELECT drinker
FROM Frequents, Serves
WHERE Frequents.bar = Serves.bar
AND (drinker, beer) IN
(SELECT * FROM Dont_like);

column1:
WITH PICKY(drinker, bar, beer) AS
(
  SELECT TOP.drinker, TOP.bar, TOP.beer
  FROM (SELECT frequents.drinker, frequents.bar, serves.beer
    FROM frequents, serves
    WHERE frequents.bar = serves.bar
  ) TOP EXCEPT
  SELECT BOTTOM.drinker, BOTTOM.bar, BOTTOM.beer
  FROM (SELECT frequents.drinker, frequents.bar, likes.beer
    FROM frequents, likes
    WHERE frequents.drinker = likes.drinker) BOTTOM
)
SELECT drinker.name
FROM drinker
EXCEPT
SELECT PICKY.drinker
FROM PICKY;

	SELECT s1.beer FROM serves s1 
	where s1.bar = f1.bar
	AND s1.beer not in
		(SELECT l1.beer from likes l1 where l1.drinker=f1.drinker)));

column1:
SELECT name AS drinker FROM Drinker 
EXCEPT 
(SELECT drinker FROM 
 (SELECT Frequents.bar, Frequents.drinker FROM Frequents, 
  (SELECT Serves.bar, foo.drinker FROM Serves, 
   (SELECT Drinker.name AS drinker, Beer.name AS beer FROM Drinker, Beer 
	EXCEPT 
	(SELECT * FROM Likes)) AS foo 
   WHERE (Serves.beer = foo.beer)) AS moo 
  WHERE (Frequents.bar = moo.bar AND Frequents.drinker = moo.drinker)) 
 AS boo);

SELECT DISTINCT name
FROM drinker

EXCEPT

SELECT DISTINCT lfsd.drinker
FROM (
	(SELECT DISTINCT lf.drinker, lfs.beer
	FROM (
		SELECT DISTINCT *
		FROM likes NATURAL JOIN frequents
	) AS lf, serves AS lfs
	WHERE (lf.bar = lfs.bar AND NOT lf.beer = lfs.beer)

	EXCEPT

	SELECT *
	FROM likes)) AS lfsd
;

select name from drinker
except all
select foo.drinker
from 
(select drinker, frequents.bar, beer
from frequents, serves
where frequents.bar = serves.bar
except all
select likes.drinker, bar, beer
from frequents, likes
where frequents.drinker = likes.drinker) as foo;

column1:
--(i) Find names of all drinkers who frequent only those bars that serve only beers they like. 
select distinct name 
from drinker d
where not exists
    (select drinker, beer  -- (drinker, beer) pairs where the drinker doesn't like the beer but the beer is served at some bar the drinker frequents
     from (frequents natural join serves) as drinks
     where drinks.drinker = d.name and beer not in (select beer from likes where drinker = drinks.drinker));

SELECT DISTINCT dr.name 
FROM Drinker dr
WHERE dr.name NOT IN (
	SELECT DISTINCT drinker FROM (
		(SELECT DISTINCT f.drinker, f.bar, s.beer
		FROM Frequents f, Serves s
		WHERE f.bar = s.bar)
		EXCEPT
		(SELECT DISTINCT l.drinker, s.bar, l.beer
		FROM Likes l, Serves s
		WHERE l.beer = s.beer)) as t);

column1:
SELECT DISTINCT name
FROM drinker
EXCEPT (
SELECT DISTINCT t.drinker
FROM (SELECT * FROM (SELECT f1.drinker, s1.beer, f1.bar
FROM frequents AS f1, serves AS s1, likes AS l1
WHERE f1.drinker = l1.drinker
AND f1.bar = s1.bar) AS ff1 EXCEPT SELECT * FROM (SELECT drinker, beer, bar
FROM frequents NATURAL JOIN serves NATURAL JOIN likes) AS ff2
	) AS t
);

/*
(drinkers who frequent only those bars that serve only beers they like) =
(drinkers) - (drinkers who frequent a bar that serves a beer they don't like).
*/

WITH TEMP1(drinker,beer) AS
(SELECT drinker,beer FROM
 frequents INNER JOIN serves ON frequents.bar = serves.bar),

TEMP2(drinker,beer) AS
(SELECT * FROM TEMP1 EXCEPT
SELECT * FROM likes)


SELECT name FROM drinker EXCEPT
SELECT drinker FROM TEMP2;

-- Find names of all drinkers who frequent 
-- only those bars that serve only beers they like.

-- select x.drinker
-- from frequents x
-- where (select * from frequents y, serves z, likes u
--                   where x.drinker=y.drinker
--                    and  y.bar = z.bar and z.beer = u.beer
--                    and y.drinker = u.drinker)

-- 1. Join frequents and serves, where the bar is the same 
-- 2. Project the drinker and the serves.beer from this. This leaves 
-- you with drinker,beer pairs.
-- Eliminate duplicates.

-- (SELECT DISTINCT drinker, serves.beer
-- FROM frequents 
-- FULL JOIN serves 
-- ON frequents.bar = serves.bar 
-- )



-- 3. Diff these drinker/beer pairs with likes.
-- This leaves you with drinker,beer pairs where drinkers 
-- do not like the beer.

-- (SELECT DISTINCT drinker, serves.beer
-- FROM frequents 
-- FULL JOIN serves 
-- ON frequents.bar = serves.bar 
-- )
-- EXCEPT
-- (
-- SELECT drinker, beer 
-- FROM likes); 



-- 4. Since you know that these drinkers do not like these beers,
-- and these beers were served at bars the drinkers went to,
-- diff all drinkers minus these drinkers. 

-- (SELECT name FROM drinker)

-- EXCEPT
-- (
-- (SELECT drinker FROM 

-- 	(SELECT DISTINCT drinker, serves.beer
-- 	FROM frequents 
-- 	FULL JOIN serves 
-- 	ON frequents.bar = serves.bar 
-- 	)
-- 	EXCEPT
-- 	(SELECT drinker, beer FROM likes)
-- )

-- AS alias
-- );


(SELECT name FROM drinker)
EXCEPT
(SELECT drinker FROM 
	((SELECT DISTINCT drinker, serves.beer
	  FROM frequents 
	  FULL JOIN serves 
	  ON frequents.bar = serves.bar)
	 EXCEPT
	 (SELECT drinker, beer FROM likes))
	AS alias);

column1:
SELECT name
FROM Drinker
-- keep drinkers who refuse to have the option to drink beer they don't like
WHERE name NOT IN (
  SELECT drinker FROM (
    -- beers drinker has options to drink at frequented bars
    SELECT drinker, beer
    FROM Frequents, Serves
    WHERE Frequents.bar = Serves.bar
    -- subtract off the ones they like
    EXCEPT
    SELECT drinker, beer
    FROM Likes
  ) as a
);
